Sentencas: Tubular electrolyte-supporting solid oxide fuel cells directly operated on carbon fuel were fabricated and tested.
Titulo: Effect of anode and Boudouard reaction catalysts on the performance of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Gadolinia doped ceria (GDC) mixed with silver was used as the anode to catalyze the electrochemical oxidation of CO while Fe-based catalyst was loaded on the carbon fuel to enhance the Boudouard reaction.
Titulo: Effect of anode and Boudouard reaction catalysts on the performance of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The performance was significantly improved, with a maximum power density of 45 mW cm(-2), 10 times higher than that of the cell without any catalyst.
Titulo: Effect of anode and Boudouard reaction catalysts on the performance of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Impedance measurements showed that the polarization resistance was decreased by tens of times through applying catalysts in the cell.
Titulo: Effect of anode and Boudouard reaction catalysts on the performance of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An operation life of 10 h was observed at a constant current of 70 mA. The mechanism of the cell reaction was analyzed.
Titulo: Effect of anode and Boudouard reaction catalysts on the performance of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells
